🟡 **MEDIUM** `formula/src/lib.rs:81` – Potentially inefficient interaction expansion
The `expand_interactions` method uses `Vec::contains` in a loop to de-duplicate terms, resulting in O(n²) complexity. For complex formulas, this could become a minor bottleneck.

→ **Fix:** Use a `HashSet` to collect unique terms, which provides O(1) average time complexity for insertions and checks, and then convert the result to a `Vec`. This is more robust and performant.

```rust
// In formula/src/lib.rs, ModelSpec::expand_interactions
use std::collections::HashSet;

pub fn expand_interactions(&mut self) {
    let mut final_terms = Vec::new();
    let mut seen_terms = HashSet::new();

    for term in &self.terms {
        match term {
            Term::FullInteraction(vars) => {
                for var in vars {
                    if seen_terms.insert(var.clone()) {
                        final_terms.push(var.clone());
                    }
                }
                let interaction_term = Term::Interaction(vars.clone());
                if seen_terms.insert(interaction_term.clone()) {
                    final_terms.push(interaction_term);
                }
            }
            _ => {
                if seen_terms.insert(term.clone()) {
                    final_terms.push(term.clone());
                }
            }
        }
    }
    self.terms = final_terms;
}
```

